2022 you were a massive year! 

I couldn’t have wished for a more magical and grounding way to round out the year than spending time with my mom and @yinchang family (with everyone’s intense work schedules, it’s rare that we were all to make the trip here at the same time) exploring our way through Taiwan, our first time back on the island in over 8 years.

SO excited to share the news that @heartofdinner is an official charity partner for this year's NYC Marathon! This is a monumental moment for the org, and can't wait to see all the magic that's about to unfold over the next 9 months leading up to the race 🙌

From @heartofdinner “As part of the TCS New York City Marathon Charity Partner Program, Heart of Dinner has been allotted 5 guaranteed, non-complementary entries. We will soon begin the process of assembling a team of passionate and heart-driven runners to represent and raise funds on behalf of Heart of Dinner and run in the marathon on November 5th, 2023 where over 50,000 runners from around the world will race through all five boroughs right here in NYC! 

It is an immense honor and privilege to look back on the humble beginnings of Heart of Dinner in a small apartment in Chinatown and, with the VITAL support of our champions, to now be able to spread our mission of tackling food insecurity and loneliness among our underserved Asian American elderly communities to the marathon’s global audience.

Heart of Dinner sources and curates nutritious and culturally thoughtful food, then packages the essential ingredients in hand-illustrated brown bags accompanied with notes of love penned in each Elder’s' native language. These signature Heart of Dinner care packages are then lovingly delivered around NYC to elderly recipients, to provide nourishment for their physical, mental, and emotional wellbeing. The population we serve are low-income and homebound, and live in socioeconomic, cultural, and linguistic isolation. These are long-standing community issues that have historically been overlooked, hence joining forces with the NYC Marathon will enable us to reach the masses about the critical work that we do to address these challenges.

STAY TUNED for more updates in the upcoming weeks, including a link to apply for the chance to run for Heart of Dinner. We are so thankful for this opportunity and for your unwavering support!”

"Work with people who deserve to work with your gift."- Catherine O'Hara

"We don't experience inclusion until we experience exclusion."- Billie Jean King

location.city_name: Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque, Abu Dhabi

social_posts.post_text:
Thank you Forbes for including a half day of touring Abu Dhabi as part of the conference and the space to connect and get to know fellow attendees (so much advice, stories of mutual career/life journeys and friendships forged on that bus!) 

We started off the tour at the Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque. This stunning piece of architecture is a masterpiece, designed in a mix of Islamic, Moorish, and Mughal architectural styles by Syrian architect Yousef Abdelky and took over a decade to build (construction beginning in 1996 and ending in 2007) and was built as a tribute to the late Sheikh Zayed bin Sultan Al Nahyan, who was the founder and first president of the United Arab Emirates.

The exterior of the mosque is made of gleaming white marble, and the minarets- goodness, each one stands at over 330 feet tall and is decorated with over 1,000 gold-colored gilded floral motifs 🤩

As we stepped inside the mosque, we were immediately struck by a sense of serenity. The interior is just as beautiful as the exterior, with chandeliers and handmade carpets in the main prayer hall is the largest hand-knotted carpet, measuring over 60,500 square feet!

social_posts.post_text:
One of my favorite experiences in the UAE, a melting pot of different cultures from around the world, has been learning about the different customary greetings, cultures, and hospitality. One experience being starting each day with a cup of Arabic coffee (Qahwa), which originated in Yemen in the 14th century and is made from lightly roasted beans brewed with spices such as cardamom, saffron, or cloves and is THE perfect complement to the sweet dates served alongside 😍

Here's a Qahwa recipe I found on http://archanaskitchen.com/:

Add lightly roasted ground coffee and water to a teapot or saucepan.

Boil the coffee vigorously on medium-high heat for 10 minutes.

Remove the pan from the heat. Crush the cardamom with the side of a knife, then add it along with the saffron to the coffee. Cover and let steep for 2-3 minutes.

Strain the coffee through a sieve into a dallah, thermos, or teapot, and serve alongside dates or sweets.
Credits: Videos 1 and 5 by @yinchang 💗

It was a privilege and a pinch me moment to have been able to spend Saturday afternoon in Washington, D.C. at a brunch co-hosted by @glamourmag and Vice President Harris at the beautiful Vice President's Residence to celebrating Women's History Month.

Being in the same space with so many accomplished and inspiring women from various industries and backgrounds provided an intimate and powerful opportunity for women to come together to celebrate and also to highlight the work that still needs to be done to achieve gender equality.

Meeting our @vp was a surreal experience that will go down as one of the most memorable moments of my life. Additionally, I am incredibly grateful for the love and support that Yin and I have received through the years from @sambarry and the Glamour family (here’s looking at you @tashpearlman @ru_wolle @hall.kathryne 💗) individually as founders/entrepreneurs and through our work together with @HeartofDinner—it was such a special moment when Sam shouted out Heart of Dinner during her passionate speech, alongside fellow attendees @theestallion, @speakerpelosi, and @ambsusanrice 🙌 (swipe to see in last slide captured by the Glamour team) 

Thank you to the wonderful @31philliplim team for styling our brunch ‘fits 💗

Still in disbelief after meeting Vice President Harris — I might as well park this photo and retire my account now 😅

Thank you @glamourmag for co-hosting this Women’s History Month brunch alongside the @vp’s team and @31philliplim for an outfit worthy of the occasion 🙏

Repost @heartofdinner 
There's no overstating how much it would mean to have you cheering alongside us this Sunday, November 5th as Heart of Dinner will be a part of the NYC Marathon as an official charity partner for the first time ever, and our extraordinary running team @ethanh2k @jatecson @long__pang @qtzion @toshnaka will be giving Heart of Dinner a global presence by running the herculean 26.2 miles in the world's most iconic running event! 

As our runners navigate the demanding stretches and all the highs and lows of the marathon, every cheer and every shout from each of you can make ALL the difference in giving them that surge of energy and vitality to keep pushing forward, all the way to the finish line, symbolizing the heart and soul of our community backing them every step of the way.

We hope to see you as part of our Brooklyn Cheer Squad and encourage you to bring your family and friends! The more, the merrier!

We’ll also be gifting the first 15 people who arrive to cheer an embroided Heart of Dinner cap, the yellow color way created exclusively for our runners & NYC cheer Squad!

Afterwards, join us at Barcade Midtown from 3:30pm-5:30pm for post-marathon celebrations with our runners!

Cheers were cheered, tears were shed and hearts are full 🙏💗

On November 28th, 2022, 
in Philly before our afternoon meetings started @yinchang and I found ourselves in Fishtown, chasing two of our favorite travel treasures: independent coffee shops and bookstores. @persimmoncoffee popped up on Google Maps and that was beginning of all the synergy that was about to unfold with the team at Persimmon Coffee (first being Yin carrying her @heartofdinner Persimmon tote lol) 

Chatting with Kai(barista/co-owner), we uncovered a beautiful connection – Persimmon Coffee had rallied behind Heart of Dinner in the early days of the pandemic in 2020 and fundraised for the mission.

Then in 2023 the stars aligned again as Yin and I were hoping to create a coffee collaboration and reached out to Persimmon Coffee, who mentioned they were about to reach out to us the same week as well with an idea – a collaboration coffee fundraiser where 100% of net proceeds would support Heart of Dinner🥰.

We’ve been so excited for this collaboration to drop! 

Introducing: Heart of Dinner with Persimmon Coffee Mexico ‘Kokoro’ coffee.

From HOD & Persimmon:

“‘Kokoro,’ translating to 'heart' in Japanese, encapsulates the shared values of love, empathy, community, and a profound respect for family legacies, uniting Persimmon and Heart of Dinner. From bean to cup, 'Kokoro' embodies our dedication to these values, echoing the love for our traditions and community bonds. 
The beans from Finca Nuevo México, chosen for their rich history and meticulous care, are artfully roasted by the Persimmon founders. The result? Notes of lychee, butterscotch, and honeycrisp apple that dance on your palate. This farm stands as a testament to a cherished family legacy dating back to 1978, lovingly tended through generations. Today, we honor Ricardo Ibarra Baumann, preserving his mother's legacy by crafting exceptional coffee.

Roast: Medium-light
Tasting notes: Lychee, butterscotch, honeycrisp apple
Perfect for: Espresso, pour over, drip.
125 bags roasted ”

Thank you to Kai, @chaereenpak & Sawyer at Persimmon Coffee for all the love put into the thoughtful roasting and packaging design, making this collab a beautiful reality (last photo from 1st meet in 2022) 💗
